Having no luck finding a Weber Smokey Mountain, I drove a little further south to Barbecues Galore.
Really, these two stores should switch names.
BBQ Island does, indeed, have barbecues galore while this place is much smaller.
They do have supplies, some grills and smokers on display, fireplaces and other stuff.
It is just on a much smaller scale than their nearby competitor.
The good thing is, normally, it is easier to have questions answered here.
Also, they actually had the smoker I was looking for.

